cinvestav.android.pki.cryptography.cert
Class X509RevokedCertificateReason

java.lang.Object
  cinvestav.android.pki.cryptography.cert.X509RevokedCertificateReason

public class X509RevokedCertificateReason
extends java.lang.Object

The reasonCode (as specified in RFC5280) is a non-critical CRL entry extension that identifies the reason for the certificate revocation. CRL issuers are strongly encouraged to include meaningful reason codes in CRL entries; however, the reason code CRL entry extension SHOULD be absent instead of using the unspecified (0) reasonCode value.
